events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 32 points, and the Dallas Mavericks matched their longest winning streak of the season at four games in a 146-111 rout of the Oklahoma City Thunder on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 32, Gafford shines in Dallas debut as Mavs thump Thunder 146-111
George and Leonard combine for 57 points in rallying Clippers past Pistons 112-106

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — The scoring and passing were impressive, though not what won over the fans in Dennis Schroder's Brooklyn Nets debut.
headlines.shortLinkText: Schroder has strong Nets debut, Brooklyn routs Spurs to spoil Wembanyama's return to draft home

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges scored 25 points, newcomer Vasilije Micic had career highs with 18 points and nine assists and the new-look Charlotte Hornets snapped a 10-game losing streak with a 115-106 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets, with help from 5 newcomers, beat Grizzlies 115-106 to end 10-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 36 points, Cole Anthony had 14 points and 11 rebounds off the bench, and the Orlando Magic turned back the Chicago Bulls 114-108 in overtime Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner scores 36 as Magic beat Bulls 114-108 in overtime

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey scored 28 points, Buddy Hield added 23 in his second game with Philadelphia and the 76ers snapped a four-game losing streak with a 119-113 victory over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey scores 28, 76ers work offensive glass in 119-113 win over Wizards

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray had 34 points and the Atlanta Hawks overcame a sluggish start to beat the Houston Rockets 122-113 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dejounte Murray scores 34 points as Hawks send Rockets to 4th straight loss, 122-113

events.name: Indiana Pacers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Myles Turner scored 23 points and Tyrese Haliburton added 22 to lead the Indiana Pacers to a 125-111 victory over the New York Knicks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Myles Turner, Tyrese Haliburton power the Pacers to a 125-111 win over the Knicks

headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen had 18 points and 15 rebounds, Evan Mobley added 17 points and 11 rebounds, and the Cleveland Cavaliers extended their winning streak to a season-high nine games by routing the Toronto Raptors 119-95 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen scores 18 points as Cavs rout Raptors 119-95, extend winning streak to season-high nine

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — As soon as Bradley Beal lunged for the steal to try to keep the ball from Stephen Curry with 3.3 seconds left, the Phoenix guard knew it was a bad gamble.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry hits 3-pointer with 0.7 seconds left, Warriors beat Suns 113-112

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Portland Trail Blazers
